The paper proposes a new method for multi-relational link prediction in knowledge graphs, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method involves decomposing the knowledge graph using a Tucker3 decomposition, which is a technique commonly used in data analysis and signal processing (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of sparsity patterns, which is a topic relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
